---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Halmetoja Model"
  description="A structural model of psychological regulation explaining how humans maintain stability through either internal integration (CENTER) or external systems (ORBIT)."
>
  <main class="home">
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Structural Psychology</p>
      <h1>The Halmetoja Model</h1>
      <p class="hero-text">
        A structural model of regulation, stability, and relational systems.
        Not all stability is the same.
      </p>

      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/halmetoja-model/" class="button button-primary">Read the Model</a>
        <a href="/articles/" class="button button-secondary">Browse Articles</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section intro">
      <div class="section-copy">
        <h2>What this model asks</h2>
        <p>
          Most psychological theories ask what a person is like.
          The Halmetoja Model asks something simpler:
        </p>
        <p class="quote">
          What happens when tension appears?
        </p>
        <p>
          From that question, everything follows:
          regulation, identity, relationships, burnout, narcissism, empathy, collapse, and integration.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="card-label">CENTER</p>
        <h3>Internal regulation</h3>
        <p class="formula">tension → held → transformed → integrated</p>
        <p>
          CENTER is not calmness.
          It is the ability to hold tension without needing immediate resolution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <p class="card-label">ORBIT</p>
        <h3>External regulation</h3>
        <p class="formula">tension → externalized → resolved through others → relief</p>
        <p>
          ORBIT is not a personality type.
          It is what happens when regulation cannot remain internal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section correction">
      <div class="section-copy narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Critical Distinction</p>
        <h2>Not all stability is CENTER</h2>
        <p>
          One of the central corrections in the model is this:
          visible stability does not automatically mean internal capacity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some systems remain stable because they can hold reality.
          Others remain stable because they simplify it.
        </p>
        <a href="/articles/the-illusion-of-stability/" class="text-link">
          Read: The Illusion of Stability
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Core Reading</p>
        <h2>Start here</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid">
        <a class="resource-card" href="/halmetoja-model/">
          <h3>The Halmetoja Model</h3>
          <p>The entry point to the whole framework.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/halmetoja-model/center-orbit-model/">
          <h3>The CENTER–ORBIT Model</h3>
          <p>Where regulation happens: inside the system or through external loops.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/halmetoja-model/narcissism-explained/">
          <h3>Narcissism Explained</h3>
          <p>Narcissism as stabilized ORBIT, maintained through mirrors rather than integration.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/halmetoja-model/mirror-economy/">
          <h3>The Mirror Economy</h3>
          <p>How relationships become distributed mirror systems for regulation.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/articles/what-regulation-actually-means/">
          <h3>What Regulation Actually Means</h3>
          <p>A structural definition of regulation as what prevents collapse under tension.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/articles/why-integration-fails/">
          <h3>Why Integration Fails</h3>
          <p>Why insight alone is not enough when the system cannot afford tension.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section articles-preview">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Latest Direction</p>
        <h2>Articles</h2>
        <a href="/articles/" class="text-link">View all articles</a>
      </div>

      <div class="grid compact">
        <a class="resource-card" href="/articles/why-avoiding-abandonment-creates-self-abandonment/">
          <h3>Why Avoiding Abandonment Creates Self-Abandonment</h3>
          <p>How preserving connection can weaken internal continuity.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/articles/why-stability-of-self-disrupts-stability-of-connection/">
          <h3>Why Stability of Self Disrupts Stability of Connection</h3>
          <p>The CENTER-side counterpart: what happens when tension is not displaced.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="resource-card" href="/articles/why-integration-fails-across-generations/">
          <h3>Why Integration Fails Across Generations</h3>
          <p>How capacity, tension, and regulation patterns pass from parent to child.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section closing">
      <div class="section-copy narrow">
        <h2>A map, not a myth</h2>
        <p>
          The Halmetoja Model is not a moral theory.
          It does not divide people into heroes and villains.
          It describes how systems behave under tension.
        </p>
        <p>
          Once regulation becomes visible, many things that once looked personal
          become structural.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .home {
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.75rem);
    line-height: 1.02;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
  }

  .hero-text {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 1.25rem auto 0;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: 180px;
    padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
    border-radius: 14px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, opacity 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease;
  }

  .button:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .button-primary {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
  }

  .button-secondary {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .section {
    margin-top: 4.5rem;
  }

  .section-copy {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .section-copy.narrow {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .section-copy h2,
  .section-heading h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .section-copy p {
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .quote {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .card,
  .resource-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.4rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease;
  }

  .card:hover,
  .resource-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.16);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
  }

  .card-label {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .card h3,
  .resource-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .card p,
  .resource-card p {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .formula {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .correction {
    padding: 1rem 0 0;
  }

  .text-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .section-heading {
    display: flex;
    align-items: end;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .section-heading .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .grid.compact .resource-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .closing {
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .split,
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .section-heading {
      align-items: start;
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .home {
      padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
    }

    .hero {
      padding-top: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-text {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .button {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>